		<p>- Chrome&#8217;s NaCl is somewhat going in the direction you suggest, but using LLVM bytecodes as substrate.<br />
- I&#8217;d prefer that we used lambda calculus instead. It&#8217;s 100% safe, and 100% equivalent to a Turing machine. (eg Haskell compiles to it)&#8230; i.e. it can&#8217;t hijack your machine which is the main objection to this idea.</p>

